Uses of Package
com.cyc.session

  • Packages that use com.cyc.session 
    Package Description
    com.cyc.base
    Interfaces for low-level interaction with Cyc; this code is not supported for external developers.
    com.cyc.baseclient
    Reference implementation of the Base Client API; this code is not supported for external developers.
    com.cyc.baseclient.api
    Provides classes for low-level interaction with Cyc; this code is not supported for external developers.
    com.cyc.baseclient.inference
    Provides classes for working with Cyc inferences; this code is not supported for external developers.
    com.cyc.baseclient.testing  
    com.cyc.baseclient.ui
    Provides Swing & AWT-based GUI components; this code is not supported for external developers.
    com.cyc.kb
    Provides basic interfaces for manipulating CycL-based java objects, both for the purpose of making assertions and for retrieving terms and values via simple queries.
    com.cyc.kb.client
    The implementation of various interfaces specified in com.cyc.kb, refer to that package for a more detailed discussion of using the API.
    com.cyc.km.query.answer.justification
    Provides the classes specific to working with justifications for Cyc inference answers.
    com.cyc.query
    Provides the core classes for constructing, specifying, and running Cyc queries.
    com.cyc.session
    The primary interfaces of the Cyc Session API.
    com.cyc.session.compatibility  
    com.cyc.session.connection
    All connection-related interfaces to be implemented by providers.
    com.cyc.session.internal
    Internal implementation classes for common Session API functionality.
    com.cyc.session.selection  
  • Classes in com.cyc.session used by com.cyc.base 
    Class and Description
    CycServerAddress
    Describes the address of a Cyc server.
    CycServerInfo
    Provides basic information about the state and location of the server to which the CycSession is connected (or was connected.) All data returned should be generated by examining the current session connection, or retrieved from the server.
    CycSession
    An active (or potentially active) session with a Cyc server.
    SessionApiException
    SessionApiException is the base exception which indicates that an application library has encountered a problem in interacting with a Cyc server.
    SessionCommandException
    SessionCommandException indicates that Session implementation code could communicate with a Cyc server, but encountered a problem issuing a command or interpreting a result.
    SessionCommunicationException
    SessionCommunicationException indicates that an application library encountered a problem when attempting to communicate with a Cyc server.
    SessionConfigurationException
    CycSessionException indicates that a Cyc session has been mis-configured or not been configured at all.
    SessionInitializationException
    SessionInitializationException indicates that a problem was encountered when initializing a CycSession.
    SessionManager
    The SessionManager is responsible for managing the lifecycle of CycSessions, from configuration, to creation, to caching, to cleanup, and providing appropriate CycSessions to API and application code that requires them.
    SessionOptions
    A set of modifiable options, such as the name of the cyclist making assertions and the project's KE purpose.
